  <div class="bulletin">
    <div class="title">The LORE Bulletin</div>
    <div class="tagline">The Depths Whisper Again</div>
    <div class="issue">Issue 003 | 11 July 2025</div>

    <div class="headline">
      <h2>Another Crew Lost. The Curse Grows Stronger.</h2>
      <div class="author">By Caspian Wren, Senior Lorekeeper of the Eastern Archives</div>
      <img src="https://i.postimg.cc/QtMsbqGF/Screenshot-2025-07-11-185802.png" alt="Treasure of the Seas">
      <p>The legend of the <b>Heart of the Depths</b> has claimed <b>yet another crew.</b></p>
      <p>Earlier this week, a rogue band of treasure hunters known as <b>The Tideborn Marauders</b> set sail in pursuit of the mythical artifact — despite warnings etched into shipwrecked logs, ancient scrolls, and even whispered from the mouths of madmen.</p>
      <p>They never returned.</p>
      <p>All that washed ashore was a cracked compass, a soaked journal, and a single message scrawled in red:</p>
      <p><b>"She watches. She waits. She drags."</b></p>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
      <!-- Left Column -->
      <div class="col-left section">
        <h3>The War Spreads: No Land Untouched</h3>
        <img src="https://i.postimg.cc/PqDK7CYT/Screenshot-2025-07-11-193106.png" alt="Evidence Board">
        <p>What began as a clash of ideals has now become a war without borders.</p>
        <p>The once-controlled skirmishes between the <b>Obsidian Order</b> and the <b>Crimson Vanguard</b> have erupted into <b>full-scale devastation</b>. Villages burn, outposts fall, and the sky rains fire as bombs continue to drop from both sides.</p>
        <p>Neutral factions are no longer safe. Reports confirm that key trading hubs — including Stonewatch Pass and Ashen Hollow — have been reduced to ruins. Even the mighty Ironridge Bastion, long thought unbreachable, now lies in rubble after a week-long siege.</p>
        <p>“The Vanguard doesn’t just want control — they want history rewritten,”</p>
        <p>said High Commander Elara, addressing a crowd of survivors in the shattered capital.</p>
        <p>Desperate calls for reinforcements echo across the server. Banners once flown in peace are now soaked in ash and crimson.</p>
        <p>Meanwhile, whispers grow of a third force — one that does not fight for land or power, but to end the war altogether… by any means necessary.</p>
        <p><b>Lines are blurred. Loyalties shift. And the world bleeds.</b></p>
        <p>This is no longer just a war.</p>
        <p><b>This is survival.</b></p>
      </div>

      <!-- Right Column -->
      <div class="col-right section">
        <h3>The Copper Golem Moves</h3>
        <img src="https://i.postimg.cc/x1bYCPLQ/Screenshot-2025-07-11-195455.png" alt="Poll Summary">
        <p>As the war rages on, something ancient stirs.</p>
        <img class="poll-chart" src="https://i.postimg.cc/Df93NXtY/Screenshot-2025-07-11-195821.png" alt="Copper Golem Chart">
        <p>Discovered in the ruins of Mechspire, a lone Copper Golem has awakened after centuries of silence. Sparks of redstone now pulse through its joints as it marches — not toward safety, but straight toward the battlefield.</p>
        <p>No one commands it.</p>
        <p>No one understands it.</p>
        <p>But both sides fear what it might do next.</p>
        <p>Is it a forgotten relic…</p>
        <p>or the war’s turning point?</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Bottom Story -->
    <div class="bottom-story">
      <h3>The Sky Cracked Open</h3>
      <img src="https://i.postimg.cc/6qgZr0qK/Screenshot-2025-07-11-201235.png" alt="Mystery">
      <p>Last night, players across the realm stopped what they were doing — as the sky tore open above Echo Ridge.</p>
      <p>A rift — glowing purple and spiraling with particles — hovered silently for exactly 3 minutes and 33 seconds. No mobs spawned. No sounds played. And then… it vanished.</p>
      <p>Locals say they felt their inventory glitch. One even claims to have seen a floating book with the title:</p>
      <p>“ENTRY 0: BEFORE CODE”</p>
      <p>The mods are silent. The admins are “investigating.” But the community wants answers.</p>
      <p>What was it?</p>
      <p>A bug?</p>
      <p>A message?</p>
      <p>Or the beginning of something bigger?</p>
      <p>Keep your eyes on the sky.</p>
      <p>It might not be the last time it opens.</p>
    </div>

    <hr style="border: none; border-top: 3px solid #000; margin: 24px 0 8px;" />
